(268, 257, 'A. Laura', 'alyson.laura@gmail.com', '', '71.199.158.86', '2006-08-24 05:00:42', '2006-08-24 04:00:42', 'wow, this blog sure has gone from Architecture to robots pretty quickly. I like it though. brings psychology in a lot more-esp that money.  this performance piece reminds me of a thesis project I saw at my school one year. this guy proposed a fully reconfigurable perfomance space that can expand/contract in size and have crosshair tracks for lighting etc. the jury torn it apart, they hated it.\nhe also created a machine that produces music in reaction to its surroundings-like what kind of noise people around it were making.  he introduced the prj with it. i loved it.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(269, 257, 'Ruairi', 'ruairiglynn@gmail.com', 'http://www.ruairiglynn.co.uk', '81.151.97.97', '2006-08-24 15:58:59', '2006-08-24 14:58:59', 'Robots, Architecture, same thing in my eyes! Im not just talking about the work of Archigram, Im thinking more in the terms of all the new transformable architecture that I feature on my site. The differences between an "inteligent" robot and an "inteligent" building are small and becoming smaller and smaller by the day.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(270, 258, 'Luke', 'phutink@hotmail.com', 'http://members.lycos.co.uk/lukecoulson/index.htm', '87.74.55.236', '2006-09-04 14:28:10', '2006-09-04 13:28:10', 'Hi\n\nYeah its a bit like a sort of animated (future) junk yard.\n\nI think perhaps there may be a practical use (as there sometimes is) for this type of art in the domain of "non lethal weapons" and or "area denial"\n\nWhere can I buy one? It may look good and serve well in my lobby to deter unwanted guests though I may have to consult the district surveyor about demolishing the "party wall" to make room foor it.\n\nPerhaps I could commission an oil painting of it and hang that on the wall as this may also have similar effect.\n\nRinaldo you say eh. Well I think he may have missed his true vocation in the "scrap" market. Sort of a "muck and brass" scenario.\n\nBut seriously folks this guy may single-handedly be sustaining the cosmetics, electronic sensor and CCTV industries business’s.\n\nI’m sure though Rinaldo maintains an inward sense of integrity in spite of his control freak preoccupations.\n\nI recommend he sends a copy of his CV/resume to Rayethon\n\nAll da best\n\nLuke', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
