(479, 372, 'Luke', 'luke.munn@gmail.com', 'http://window.org.nz', '202.89.32.246', '2008-02-14 02:55:29', '2008-02-14 02:55:29', 'A fascinating project indeed, but I have to object to their second point. Air will be public space? Building facades public space? Neither their website nor their video extrapolates this point, which - taken at face value - is the ridiculous masquerading as a sweeping statement on the future. The former is totally public, indeed the one resource which is free and lacking in boundaries (as So Cal states bickering over air quality infecting their territory can attest to). The latter again doesn''t make sense without any explanation. Even extending the definition of ''facade'' to include corporate lobbies, foyers, courtyards, and entranceways, this is a miniscule amount of space. Most of this is also far from public, remaining on private land and so restricting behaviour, freedoms, and lingering to what the owner deems ''appropriate''. Protesters at local malls typically last about 5 minutes before their ''public'' space suddenly becomes very exclusive.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
