om/biocv.html">Eric Singer</a> and there are links to other pioneers.\n\n<strong>Floor Pads</strong>\n\n<a href="http://www.interactivearchitecture.org/physical-computing%e2%80%99s-greatest-hits-and-misses.html/electroland-2" rel="attachment wp-att-1212"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1212" title="electroland" src="http://www.interactivearchitecture.org/2009/electroland.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="230" /></a>\n<a href="http://electroland.net/">Electroland </a>\n\n<strong>Video Mirrors (This that make people wave their hands)</strong>\n\n<object width="450" height="253" classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=3576457&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=1&amp;show_byline=0&amp;show_portrait=0&amp;color=ffffff&amp;fullscreen=1" /><embed width="450" height="253" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" src="http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=3576457&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=1&amp;show_byline=0&amp;show_portrait=0&amp;color=ffffff&amp;fullscreen=1" allowfullscreen="true" allowscriptaccess="always" /></object>\n\n<a href="http://www.msavisuals.com/body_paint">Memo''s ''Body Paint''</a> can be seen at the Decode Exhibition at the V&amp;A Gallery in London.\n\n<strong>Mechanical Pixels</strong>\n\n<a href="http://www.interactivearchitecture.org/physical-computing%e2%80%99s-greatest-hits-and-misses.html/hyposurface" rel="attachment wp-att-1217"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1217" title="hyposurface" src="http://www.interactivearchitecture.org/2009/hyposurface-450x359.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="359" /></a>\n\n<object width="450" height="350" classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowScriptAccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/JSZg9zgdCSM&amp;color1=0xb1b1b1&amp;color2=0xcfcfcf&amp;hl=en_US&amp;feature=player_embedded&amp;fs=1" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><embed width="450" height="350" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/JSZg9zgdCSM&amp;color1=0xb1b1b1&amp;color2=0xcfcfcf&amp;hl=en_US&amp;feature=player_embedded&amp;fs=1" allowFullScreen="true" allowScriptAccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" allowscriptaccess="always" /></object>\n\nOkay I''ve gone for a classic here choosing the Hyposurface example mainly because I find the commentary on this video funny. There is much better footage online about this project and of course there are many other examples of this kind of work physical pixels such as <a href="http://www.flare-facade.com/">FLARE</a> and <a href="http://www.aether.hu/pgl/">Ping genius loci</a>.\n\n<strong>Scooby-Doo paintings</strong> (Artworks that react to presence)\n\n<object width="450" height="253" classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=9333075&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=1&amp;show_byline=0&amp;show_portrait=0&amp;color=ffffff&amp;fullscreen=1" /><embed width="450" height="253" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" src="http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=9333075&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=1&amp;show_byline=0&amp;show_portrait=0&amp;color=ffffff&amp;fullscreen=1" allowfullscreen="true" allowscriptaccess="always" /></object>\n\n‘<a href="http://www.cinimodstudio.com/flutter">Flutter</a>’ by Cinimod Studio plays with the encounter virtual butterflies. The artwork is a product of their on-going fascination with the motion of a butterfly’s flight and the iridescent reflections and scattering of light by the scales on a butterfly’s wing.\n\nBody as Cursor (Tracking and Drawing)\n\nHand as Cursor (Minority Report)\n\nMultitouch Interfaces\n\nTilty Stands and Tables\n\nTilty Controllers\n\nThings You Yell At\n\nHuge dancefloor generating Live visuals controlled by performers voice and other instruments for a range of songs within a set list. In collaboration with U2 lighting designer Willie Williams, <a href="http://www.jasonbruges.com/projects/uk-projects/george-michael-live">Jason Bruges Studio</a> designed the system for George Michael’s live shows.\n\n<a href="http://www.interactivearchitecture.org/physical-computing%e2%80%99s-greatest-hits-and-misses.html/bruges" rel="attachment wp-att-1209"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1209" title="bruges" src="http://www.interactivearchitecture.org/2009/bruges.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="363" /></a>\n\nmeditation helpers\nfields of grass (running your hand across it affects it)\ndolls and pets\nremote hugs\n17. LED fetishism', 'Physical Computing’s Greatest Hits (and misses)', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1206-autosave', '', '', '2012-04-15 14:03:44', '2012-04-15 14:03:44', '', 1206, 'http://ia.local/1206-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
